These divorces are occurring mainly, though not exclusively, among the younger generation. The increase in divorce rates may be due to gaining a better understanding of personal rights. As Al Jazeera reported earlier this year, some lawyers dealing with divorces in Saudi Arabia have also pointed to conflict based on gender as another reason for divorce cases. At the same time, however, there has been a marked increase in apprehension regarding divorce, and some wonder if the end of this year will bring even greater increases in divorce rates.
